<div class="question">How do you get the high-res (1920x1080) web pages on the FireTV?  My web pages think it is 960x520</div>
<div class="answer">
<p>This was tough to figure out, but is pretty easy if you can control the <code>viewport</code> meta tag in the HTML and are using 
your own app (i.e. not the WASK thing) with a WebView you can tweak.</p>

<p>First: in the app, <code>WebSettings.setUseWideViewport(true)</code>.</p>

<p>Second: make sure the viewport has <code>initial-scale=0.5</code>.</p>

<p>Here are some test pages with various viewport settings:</p>

{{#each tests}}
<p><a href="/tests/{{this}}.html" class="btn btn-outline-primary">{{this}}</a></p>
